From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: James Shkolnik <jshkolnik@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 12 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] orangepi4pro: disable AXP515 BMU (no battery)

The AXP515 battery-management PMIC probe fails (-22, "failed to add irq chip";
U-Boot also can't read it). This is a headless DC-powered board with no battery
use case. Disabling the node removes the failed probe + dummy-regulator noise.
NOTE: pmu1 nominally provides reg_drivevbus (USB OTG vbus); since its probe
already fails those consumers fall back to dummy regulators, so behaviour is
unchanged. If a USB-OTG-vbus regression appears, drop this patch.

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/allwinner/sun60i-a733-orangepi-4-pro.dts b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/allwinner/sun60i-a733-orangepi-4-pro.dts
index 4468cc2e6..989b2195a 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/allwinner/sun60i-a733-orangepi-4-pro.dts
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/allwinner/sun60i-a733-orangepi-4-pro.dts
@@ -1803,7 +1803,7 @@ &s_twi0 {
 	pmu1: pmu@34 {
 		compatible = "x-powers,axp515";
 		reg = <0x34>;
-		status = "okay";
+		status = "disabled"; /* OPi4Pro: no battery/BMU; probe fails -22 */
 		interrupts = <0 IRQ_TYPE_LEVEL_LOW>;
 		interrupt-parent = <&nmi_intc>;
 		x-powers,drive-vbus-en;
